# Consistent LF line endings in the repo AND working tree — matches rustfmt
# (`newline_style = "Unix"`). Without this, git's Windows autocrlf writes CRLF on
# checkout, which breaks `cargo fmt --check` and byte-exact output tests.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Raw-byte fuzz seed corpus — NEVER normalize (some files are intentionally
# invalid UTF-8 / contain control bytes; line-ending conversion would corrupt them).
fuzz/corpus/** binary

# Belt-and-suspenders: these are never text.
*.exe binary
*.pdb binary
*.png binary

# Real-disc CI fixtures (crates/bdinfo-rs/tests/fixtures). The BDMV folder bytes
# and the .iso are opaque binary — a CRLF/LF rewrite would corrupt the M2TS / CLPI /
# MPLS / index streams and break parsing, the very cross-platform failure these
# guard against. The golden reports carry the report's locked CRLF byte contract,
# so they must keep their exact bytes too (`-text` disables eol conversion while
# still diffing as text). Without these, `* text=auto eol=lf` above would clobber
# both on checkout.
crates/bdinfo-rs/tests/fixtures/BigBuckBunny/** binary
crates/bdinfo-rs/tests/fixtures/*.iso binary
crates/bdinfo-rs/tests/fixtures/golden/*.txt -text diff

# The wasm crate's measured-scan parity golden carries the same locked CRLF
# report bytes; keep them verbatim (the wasm test compares raw bytes).
crates/bdinfo-rs-wasm/tests/*.txt -text diff
